tafsir[6]{c,v,t}:
  68,16,"I will place a mark on his nose which will stick with him and disfigure him."
  68,24,"They were saying to one another: “No poor person should come to you at the garden today.”"
  68,27,"“Nay! We have been deprived of harvesting our crops because of us having been determined to prevent the poor from eating them.”"
  68,30,"So they began to go back on their words out of regret."
  68,37,"Do you have a book in which you read that there should be equality between the obedient and disobedient?"
  68,40,"O Messenger! Ask those making these statement: “Who is their guarantor for this?”"